description: Description

Shaolinq is a thoughtfully designed ORM and Linq provider for .NET
    
Use this package to add Shaolinq and out-of-the-box Postgres support (via the DotConnect ADO.NET Postgres provider).
    
Designed to perform super fast and be easy to use, Shaolinq's features also include:
    
- First class schema-first ORM with WYSIWYG data access and minipulation.
- First class LINQ support (not the basic kind you see in most other OSS projects).
- Single trip updating of objects.
- Support for Sqlite, MySql and Postgres.
- Automatic database creation and schema migration.
- Delete LINQ extension for batch server side deletes.
- Full support for server side date functions (Date.DayOfWeek etc).
- Easily extensible with a simple interface for adding support for other ADO.NET compatible databases.
- Open Source!
summary: A thoughtful ORM and Linq provider for .NET and Postgres (via the DotConnect Postgres provider)

description:
==============================================================================

This is a snnipet to connect to some Intelipost webservices and make easier your integration.

Intelipost is a technology & consulting company based in São Paulo, Brazil that offers a Logistics Gateway API and provides SAAS to many e-commerce webshops that are willing to optimize their logistics overall costs.

Intelipost connects your webshop to all main brazilian logistics providers and supports most used ERP solutions.

The main features intelipost offers for your business:
+ Freight comparison using our proprietary algorithm
+ Daily updates of freight costs, delivery time & addresses
+ Custom tracking page of your webshop
+ Automatic Correios refund in case of delays (brazilian postal company)
+ BI Reports
+ And more!
The major benefits:
+ Activate new logistics providers easily
+ Measure the Quality Score of each provider
+ Cost reduction from 5%- 40% in shipping costs p. order
+ Reduce IT dev & maintenance costs
+ And more!
Interested, but still have some doubts?

Access our documentation available at our official technical wiki (https://docs.intelipost.com.br) or at Github (https://github.com/intelipost).

==============================================================================
